1
00:00:06,033 --> 00:00:07,500
<i>- Sir, you almost...
- Hey, keep it down!</i>

2
00:00:07,633 --> 00:00:09,333
<i>What matters is that
you didn't do anything.</i>

3
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,167
<i>The board has decided
to hire someone</i>

4
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>to help the current crisis
ng company.</i>

5
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:14,033
<i> Good afternoon, everyone.</i>

6
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:16,300
<i>I'm Aldrin Castelo
of Castelo Prime Holdings.</i>

7
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:19,067
<i>Why hasn't your daughter
just died already?</i>

8
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,300
<i> Ow! What the...</i>

9
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:23,467
<i>Don't drag
into your nasty attitude!</i>

10
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,400
<i> - my daughter
- Her body is starting to reject</i>

11
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> the current medication.</i>

12
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,500
<i> I think we need to consider</i>

13
00:00:29,633 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>the experimental treatment
in Hong Kong.</i>

14
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:33,200
<i> A risk is still a risk.</i>

15
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,267
<i>Your daughter could die
because of it.</i>

16
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:36,500
<i>I don't want to gamble
with that.</i>

17
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,433
<i>Think about it again,
Mrs. Torrecampo.</i>

18
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:40,933
<i>I can't stand seeing my daughter
suffer anymore.</i>

19
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:43,233
<i>Maybe I need to take her
to Hong Kong.</i>

20
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:45,300
<i> Doesn't Paolo disagree?</i>

21
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:47,700
<i>What matters
is my daughter's life,</i>

22
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:50,200
<i> not my husband's feelings.</i>

23
00:00:57,967 --> 00:00:59,500
Ashley.

24
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:00,733
Auntie Marj.

25
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:02,433
I saw in the visitor's log

26
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:05,567
that you and Xander
visited Jasmine.

27
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,533
Don't you know I've forbidden
that guy from seeing her?

28
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,833
And you brought him there.

29
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:14,600
I'm sorry, Auntie Marj.

30
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:17,067
We just wanted to see Jasmine.

31
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:20,400
We miss her, and we're worried.

32
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:23,300
Because of you,
my daughter got stressed.

33
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,467
Do you know she had a seizure?

34
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:30,300
The doctor said your visit
might have triggered it.

35
00:01:30,433 --> 00:01:31,700
Please forgive me, Auntie Marj.

36
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,933
I'm so sorry,
I didn't mean to.

37
00:01:34,567 --> 00:01:35,767
I'm really sorry, Auntie.

38
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,367
Hey, Marj!

39
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:39,467
What are you doing
to my daughter?

40
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,033
Who gave you the right to yell
at her and make her cry?

41
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,933
I'm just scolding your daughter

42
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:46,833
because she did something wrong.

43
00:01:46,967 --> 00:01:49,233
She put my child in danger.

44
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:50,667
Wow!

45
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,833
So it's okay when you do it?

46
00:01:52,967 --> 00:01:55,167
But last time when I said
something to your kid,

47
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,267
you almost dragged my arm!

48
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:04,300
How about I stab you with this
fork so we're even?

49
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,800
- Mom, please stop!
- Shut up! Go upstairs!

50
00:02:06,933 --> 00:02:07,933
Now!

51
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:12,133
What now, Marj?

52
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:14,633
Where's that courage of yours?

53
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,767
Why can't you say anything?

54
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,133
Go ahead.

55
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:07,600
Stab me so everyone can see
what a demon you are,

56
00:03:07,733 --> 00:03:09,400
and your true colors!

57
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:11,167
Oh my, Ma'am Thea!

58
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,333
Ma'am Thea! Please stop!

59
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:14,167
- That's enough!
- You think I'm scared of you?

60
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,300
Ma'am Thea, please stop!

61
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,033
Remember this.

62
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:24,033
If you ever yell
at my daughter again,

63
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:26,733
even if Dad and Mom
try to stop me,

64
00:03:26,867 --> 00:03:29,633
I won't hesitate to hurt you.

65
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:41,767
Ma'am Marj, are you okay?

66
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:43,967
I'm really going to report her
to Sir Paolo.

67
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:46,067
What she's doing to you isn't
right!

68
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,600
Ma'am Yolly, don't bother.

69
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,200
Paolo and I already
have enough problems.

70
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:53,667
I won't waste my time
and attention on that woman.

71
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:57,000
Jasmine is what matters.

72
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:13,467
Marj.

73
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:17,000
I thought you were
at the hospital.

74
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:21,500
I asked Weng to watch Jasmine
for now.

75
00:04:22,867 --> 00:04:24,433
I was actually going
to ask you to go,

76
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:26,233
but I know you're busy.

77
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:27,900
Marj...

78
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,367
I know I told you

79
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:33,833
I'd lie low at work
for a while so...

80
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:43,933
What's going on?

81
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,767
You're booking a flight
to Hong Kong?

82
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:51,567
Didn't we already talk
about this?

83
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:54,867
Paolo, our daughter
is getting worse.

84
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:58,667
I'm just looking for a way
to save her.

85
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,433
Did you know she had a seizure
earlier?

86
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,500
Her medications aren't working.

87
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,500
Why didn't you call me?

88
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:07,067
I did!

89
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,633
Didn't your secretary tell you?

90
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,733
You could've texted me!

91
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:15,633
I know you're busy,
so I made the decision myself.

92
00:05:15,767 --> 00:05:18,567
If I don't act now,
Jasmine will suffer.

93
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,900
What if your daughter's
condition gets worse

94
00:05:21,033 --> 00:05:22,533
because of that?

95
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:24,300
Marj, you're not listening
to me.

96
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:26,033
You're ignoring my opinion.

97
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:28,933
This is unbelievable.

98
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:33,667
Is no one going to listen to me
even here?

99
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,767
Don't I have a voice in this
house, either?

100
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,600
Your voice?

101
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:40,933
That's what you're worried
about right now?

102
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:46,067
Paolo, I just told you
our daughter had a seizure!

103
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:48,367
And you're still thinking
about yourself?

104
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,800
This is not about you!

105
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:52,967
This isn't about you needing
to control everything.

106
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:55,467
This is about Jasmine
and keeping her alive!

107
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,267
I'm trying to keep
her alive, too.

108
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,667
That's why I won't agree
to what you want.

109
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,667
Marj, don't defy me...

110
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:11,167
if you don't want us to fight.

111
00:06:16,067 --> 00:06:18,733
If you won't come
to Hong Kong, fine.

112
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:23,333
But don't stop me from trying
to save our daughter's life.

113
00:06:48,133 --> 00:06:50,100
Marj, what do you think
you're doing?

114
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,700
Jasmine and I are leaving, Mom.

115
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:55,967
You can't!
Didn't Paolo already say no?

116
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:57,167
Put that back upstairs!

117
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,367
No, no, wait.

118
00:06:58,933 --> 00:06:59,967
Come on, Marj!

119
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,333
- Mom!
- Marj, you can't leave!

120
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:03,400
- Come on!
- Mom!

121
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:05,433
- Mom, please listen to me!
- Come on!

122
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:07,500
Grandma, Auntie Marj,
please stop!

123
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:09,633
Mom, I'm Jasmine's mother.

124
00:07:09,767 --> 00:07:12,333
I have the right to decide
for her.

125
00:07:12,467 --> 00:07:14,367
And Paolo is the head
of the family.

126
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:17,367
Why can't you just obey
your husband?

127
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:20,500
No one can stop me
from curing my daughter!

128
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,433
Not even you!
Give me my bag, Mom!

129
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,200
- Please stop, Auntie Marj.
- Marj!

130
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,333
Mom!

131
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,433
- Marj!
- Grandma.

132
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,700
Grandma, are you okay?

133
00:07:33,467 --> 00:07:34,500
Yolly!

134
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:36,233
My phone!

135
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,467
Paolo.

136
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:50,233
More prospective clients
for Menagerie.

137
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,900
I used my Dad's connections.

138
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:01,400
Why are you only showing me
this now?

139
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,833
Because they're my last resort.

140
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:10,633
Honestly, they're like
Mr. Lorenzo.

141
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,767
They'll agree to buy
the property

142
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,233
just because I said so.

143
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:19,933
Seriously, Thea?

144
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,467
What do you have on these
people?

145
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:26,700
How are you convincing them
like this?

146
00:08:27,467 --> 00:08:28,967
Are you blackmailing them, too?

147
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:38,067
Paolo, what I have with these
men are far worse.

148
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,100
So don't ask.

149
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:43,667
- Thea.
- But I told them

150
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:46,867
you'd meet them,

151
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,833
before they close
the deal with us.

152
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:51,867
No.

153
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:57,533
I don't want to close a deal
based on blackmail.

154
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,600
Then tell me what to do
to help you.

155
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,367
Paolo, you need to defeat Aldrin

156
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,767
and prove to the board that
they were wrong to hire him!

157
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,500
Hello, Mom?

158
00:09:18,233 --> 00:09:21,633
Paolo, your wife just left
with luggage.

159
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:24,100
She said she's taking Jasmine
to Hong Kong.

160
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:25,233
What?

161
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:27,900
What's going on?

162
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:33,000
Paolo!

163
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:44,733
Mom...

164
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,467
do I really need this?

165
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,933
I can walk.

166
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:52,600
Sweetheart,
we need to save your energy.

167
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:53,833
When we get to the airport,

168
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:56,367
we'll also ask
for wheelchair assistance.

169
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:58,367
You might faint.

170
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,733
Where's Dad?

171
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:05,733
Shouldn't he be here?

172
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,800
He's just busy with work.

173
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,733
We can do this, okay?

174
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:21,500
Are you sure?

175
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,567
Of course.

176
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:31,533
I promise, your dad will follow
once everything's okay.

177
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:49,533
That woman.

178
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:50,800
She essentially kidnapped

179
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,200
her own daughter!
Our granddaughter!

180
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:54,367
We should report her
to the police

181
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,167
so Marj gets a blotter.

182
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,900
So, the moment they land
in Hong Kong,

183
00:10:58,033 --> 00:10:59,700
she can get arrested.

184
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:01,967
Stop overreacting, Regina.

185
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:05,167
Besides, do you really want
to drag our name into this?

186
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:09,433
The news will spread
if something blows up.

187
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:12,067
We can't afford
any more trouble.

188
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,000
What if they never come back?

189
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:16,700
Or what if something happens
to Jasmine?

190
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:19,967
Oh, Paolo, what's that?

191
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,600
I'm going to Hong Kong
to follow Marj and Jasmine.

192
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,367
Oscar, put that back.

193
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,000
No, no.

194
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,267
Leave it.

195
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:36,700
The company is in the middle
of a crisis, Paolo.

196
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:40,800
You complain that I kept you
in the dark,

197
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:42,700
and now you're leaving?

198
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:45,300
Dad, I should be
with my family right now!

199
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,200
We've been your family
from the start.

200
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:53,000
Let Marj do her job.

201
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:56,133
Stay here and do yours!

202
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:59,767
That's the only way the two
of you can save Jasmine!

203
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,800
There you go again, Dad.

204
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:03,500
Ordering me around.

205
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,500
Tell me, Dad.

206
00:12:05,633 --> 00:12:07,533
When was the last time
you valued

207
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:09,867
my opinion or my decisions
at work?

208
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:14,100
You want me here,
but you don't respect me

209
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,100
as part of this company!

210
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:19,500
Greg, stop it!

211
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:27,767
So this must be how Edward
feels every time right, Dad?

212
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,733
Greg!

213
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:41,600
If you leave the company now,

214
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:43,400
forget about your position.

215
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:51,433
You will stop being a CEO
and you will be like Edward.

216
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,400
unable to come back
even as a janitor!

217
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:01,800
Let's see where you, your wife,
and your daughter end up.

218
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:18,100
We'll administer a concentrated
immune booster to Jasmine.

219
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:20,900
The injection itself,
it won't hurt much.

220
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,433
Pero once the medicine
starts working,

221
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:25,000
her body will react.

222
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:29,333
Dr. Marquez, you mean...

223
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:31,700
she'll still feel pain?

224
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:32,767
Yes.

225
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:35,467
She will feel pain because
the immune system

226
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:39,233
is being pushed to work harder
than the usual.

227
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:45,267
So if I sign this...

228
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:49,633
I'm basically agreeing
to let her suffer again.

229
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:04,833
Mommy, I'm scared.

230
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,000
Me too, sweetheart.

231
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,333
I'm really worried.

232
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,733
But if I don't do anything,

233
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:14,533
her condition might get worse.

234
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:19,100
It feels like
there's no right decision.

235
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:23,833
Whatever I choose,
my daughter gets hurt.

236
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:27,033
But Jasmine, listen to me.

237
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:29,200
If this treatment works,

238
00:14:29,367 --> 00:14:31,667
we won't have to be scared
like this again.

239
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,800
You won't have to suffer
anymore.

240
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:37,000
So be brave, okay?

241
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,567
So you can get better.

242
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,467
Hello, Paolo?

243
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,933
Marj, what do you think
you're doing?

244
00:15:55,033 --> 00:15:57,367
<i>I told you,
I don't have a choice.</i>

245
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,600
I said I'd do anythin
for our daughter.

246
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,433
Do you even know if you can
trust that doctor?

247
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:09,400
Yes, Edward's friend
is an expert in this field.

248
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,867
<i> So what now?</i>

249
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,533
So you and my dear brother
planned this together?

250
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,700
You went behind my back!

251
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:20,100
Behind your back?

252
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,467
You already knew
I made my decision.

253
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,300
There was no conspiracy.

254
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:25,867
And please don't play
the victim.

255
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,767
This isn't about you.

256
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,800
Marj, you're missing my point.

257
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:34,267
You and my brother decided
without telling me!

258
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:37,667
There's no point arguing
with you anymore.

259
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,933
You're just upset
because of that same issue.

260
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,633
You think I never listen to you.

261
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:44,567
<i> Which is true, isn't it?</i>

262
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:49,033
This isn't about our daughter's
condition.

263
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:50,933
This is about you feeling like

264
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:53,333
you've lost control over
your daughter and me.

265
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:56,500
Marj, I am warning you.

266
00:16:56,633 --> 00:16:59,167
Okay, okay,
let's talk later.

267
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:01,133
Just wait for my text.

268
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:03,700
Marj!

269
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:05,567
Hello, Marj!

270
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:19,367
Che, that faith healer
you took me to seems suspicious.

271
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:21,867
Even the place looked shady.

272
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:26,500
No, Ma'am Yolly,
Madame Elsa is effective.

273
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,667
I promise, my friend's boyfriend

274
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:29,733
had liver disease.

275
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:31,100
She cured him.

276
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:33,233
I swear, Madame Elsa is legit.

277
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,600
So, how much donation they gave?

278
00:17:35,733 --> 00:17:37,167
Around one hundred thousand.

279
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,533
One hundred thousand?

280
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:41,033
Oh my God, Cheche!

281
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,433
That's so much!

282
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:44,767
It would take me forever
to save that!

283
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:46,800
But Ma'am, think about it.

284
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:47,967
If you go to a doctor,

285
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,567
you'll spend way more.

286
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:53,900
Think of it this way,
bigger donation, better chances.

287
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:55,667
But what if she can't cure me?

288
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:59,200
Didn't Madame Elsa say that

289
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:01,933
if you're not healed
within a week,

290
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:03,600
she'll give your money back?

291
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:07,333
But it's up to you, Ma'am.

292
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,200
- Jasmine, Jasmine.
- Relax, relax.

293
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,833
It's okay, it's okay.

294
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:29,633
- Calm down.
- It's okay, it's okay.

295
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:30,633
Sweetheart, please.

296
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:32,933
It just means the medicine
is working.

297
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,000
It's okay, it's okay.

298
00:18:34,133 --> 00:18:36,767
- Just calm down.
- I want to go home.

299
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:42,167
Mommy, it hurts.

300
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:45,367
Please help me! I'm hurting!
I don't want this anymore!

301
00:18:45,500 --> 00:18:46,500
Calm down.

302
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,900
- Jas...
- Please relax.

303
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:52,300
- Please relax.
- Jasmine, please.

304
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,600
It just means the medicine
is working.

305
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:55,833
Come on.

306
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:57,867
- Just breathe.
- I want to go home!

307
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,667
Please, just get me out of here!

308
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,600
It's too painful!

309
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,500
Mom, please!
Promise, I'll be good!

310
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:06,700
I won't disobey you
or Dad anymore!

311
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,333
Please, just make it stop!

312
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:09,733
Sweetheart, listen to me.

313
00:19:09,867 --> 00:19:12,133
- Just a little longer.
- I want to go home!

314
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:13,533
I want Daddy!

315
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:16,633
I want home,
why did you bring me here?

316
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:18,467
I can't take it!

317
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:24,700
Jasmine.

318
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,367
Hello? Yes, hon.

319
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:30,967
I'm already in the lobby,
oay, I'll wait for you.

320
00:19:31,133 --> 00:19:32,100
Okay.

321
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:36,067
You.

322
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:39,567
Are you the one putting ideas
into my wife's head?

323
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:42,967
What are you talking about?

324
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:45,700
My wife defied me
because of you.

325
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,033
Defied you?

326
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,333
What are you,

327
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:51,067
Marj's parent?
Why would she have to obey you?

328
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:52,700
Don't come any closer!

329
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,033
Let go of me!

330
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:56,967
You poisoned my wife's mind,

331
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,433
that's why she went
to Hong Kong!

332
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,100
Are you doing this on purpose?

333
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:01,867
Are you doing this to spite me?

334
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:03,967
I didn't push her into anything.

335
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,533
That was her own decision.

336
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:07,433
It just so happened
that I could help her.

337
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:08,400
Let go of me!

338
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:11,267
And why would I refuse to help

339
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,433
a mother who just wants
to save her child?

340
00:20:14,567 --> 00:20:16,067
Let go of me!

341
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,700
- Come on! Let go of me!
- Come on!

342
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,667
Stop it!

343
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,233
Both of you, stop!

344
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:24,033
- What!
- What are you doing?

345
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,600
You're acting like children!

346
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:29,133
And here in the office,
of all places?

347
00:20:29,267 --> 00:20:30,833
Aren't you ashamed?

348
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,400
Your husband started it!

349
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:34,767
He convinced Marj to take
our daughter to Hong Kong.

350
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,867
Even though I said she couldn't!

351
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,633
That's not true!

352
00:20:39,767 --> 00:20:42,200
If you believe that,
then you're basically saying

353
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:43,833
Marj is stupid enough
to be manipulated!

354
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,200
That's enough!

355
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:50,433
He's right, Paolo.

356
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:52,867
It was Marj's
own reckless decision.

357
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,733
You shouldn't blame Edward
for her mistake.

358
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:02,833
This is the last time
you interfere with my family.

359
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:05,000
Because next time,
I won't back down.

360
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:06,700
Do you understand?

361
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,500
Edward! Edward!

362
00:21:39,633 --> 00:21:41,633
- What?
- You shouldn't be meddling

363
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,667
in Marj and Paolo's problems!

364
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,567
Look, you just started a fight!

365
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:46,800
He was the one who came at me!

366
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,133
I don't care!

367
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:51,200
Why did you even have to help
Marj and Jasmine in Hong Kong?

368
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:53,933
What is this? Are you trying
to impress Marj?

369
00:21:55,167 --> 00:21:56,867
What?

370
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:00,933
You think I don't know?

371
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:04,900
You never got closure
with Marj, did you?

372
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:06,933
You've liked her
for a long time,

373
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:09,033
and that never really
went away.

374
00:22:09,167 --> 00:22:12,367
And now that Paolo doesn't agree
with what Marj wants,

375
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:15,567
here you are acting like her
knight in shining armor.

376
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,500
Why?

377
00:22:17,633 --> 00:22:20,133
So you can score points
with her?

378
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:22,933
Don't twist my help into
something else to my niece.

379
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:24,900
They're my family,
your family, too!

380
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,333
Shouldn't you be helping them,
too?

381
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:28,800
And because of that help,

382
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:30,300
everything's a mess now!

383
00:22:30,867 --> 00:22:32,167
There you go again, Edward.

384
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:33,933
Once again,
you did the wrong thing.

385
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,733
Is that really how low
you think of me?

386
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:41,000
I'm not the only one who thinks
that way about you.

387
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:44,500
Everyone sees you that way.

388
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:46,400
Even Marj.

389
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:49,967
That's why she didn't
choose you, right?

390
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:58,600
<i>So you've already made
your decision.</i>

391
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:00,133
Happy?

392
00:23:10,533 --> 00:23:11,600
- Ma'am
- Oh?

393
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,067
Can I ask you something?

394
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,767
Why did you suddenly
change your mind?

395
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:17,533
I debated with myself
for a long time.

396
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:22,300
Then I realized...
if she can heal me,

397
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:24,567
maybe she can heal Jasmine, too.

398
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:28,800
Oh, yes, that makes sense.

399
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:30,833
But I should be the first one
to try it.

400
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,433
Here.

401
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:35,467
- Oh.
- Ma'am,

402
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,433
where did that come from?

403
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:38,567
That's a lot...
That's a lot of money!

404
00:23:39,533 --> 00:23:40,633
This was supposed
to be the down payment

405
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:43,133
for the land I'm planning
to buy in the province.

406
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:45,800
So I really hope that believing

407
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,667
in Madame Elsa turns out
to be the right choice.

408
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,567
Okay then, Ma'am.

409
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:53,400
Let's go,
hide it first.

410
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:55,233
All right, let's go.

411
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:01,633
So...

412
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:04,500
you want my help
to beat my brother?

413
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:07,800
But I don't work in the
Torrecampo Realty anymore.

414
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:13,100
And seriously, you want me
to go against my own brother?

415
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:20,067
Let's not kid ourselves, Edward.

416
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:22,267
I know, you just like me,

417
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,967
that you and your brother
don't exactly get along.

418
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:29,367
Actually, I've always wondered

419
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:31,967
why you're not part
of your family's company.

420
00:24:32,833 --> 00:24:34,967
And after seeing your fight
the other day...

421
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:37,467
everything makes sense.

422
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,333
I get it.

423
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:44,833
And your point is?

424
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:48,033
If you help me beat
your brother...

425
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:51,867
wouldn't that be
your revenge, too?

426
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:56,733
That's it?

427
00:24:56,867 --> 00:24:59,933
And if I'm successful
with this project,

428
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:02,967
I will get a coveted
executive position

429
00:25:03,133 --> 00:25:04,500
at the Torrecampo Realty.

430
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:10,767
The board loves me, Edward.

431
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:13,533
It wouldn't be impossible for me
to replace your brother

432
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:14,733
in the company.

433
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:19,400
And if that happens, who knows,

434
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:21,733
Maybe I'll give you
a good position.

435
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:24,533
A well-deserved one.

436
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:45,033
Doctor, I'm sorry.

437
00:25:45,167 --> 00:25:46,300
I didn't expect

438
00:25:46,433 --> 00:25:49,200
my daughter would have to go
through something this hard.

439
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:50,700
We've already done
several rounds,

440
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:53,333
but her condition
still hasn't improved.

441
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:56,600
I can't bear watching
my daughter suffer anymore.

442
00:25:56,733 --> 00:25:58,767
We'll just go back
to the Philippines

443
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:01,000
to consider other treatments.

444
00:26:01,133 --> 00:26:04,300
You didn't just ignore
your husband with what you did.

445
00:26:04,433 --> 00:26:07,800
You also disrespected us.

446
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:09,567
But honestly, Marj...

447
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:12,233
it feels like you're the one
killing our daughter.

448
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:14,700
Just like how you killed
our relationship!

449
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:18,933
You know what's funny?

450
00:26:19,067 --> 00:26:20,167
They assume that

451
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:23,467
just because the properties
carry the Torrecampo name,

452
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,300
they'll sell easily.

453
00:26:25,433 --> 00:26:27,700
They can't even fix
their own family.

454
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:29,300
How can they run a company?

455
00:26:29,433 --> 00:26:32,433
Shut your foul mouth!

456
00:26:32,567 --> 00:26:34,467
Paolo!

457
00:26:36,567 --> 00:26:40,200
Marj, the problem is that both
of you are hurt.

458
00:26:40,333 --> 00:26:42,500
You're both carrying so much
resentment.

459
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:47,000
Don't let your family
fall apart.

460
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:50,367
I thought I was choosing
what was best for you.

461
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:54,267
But maybe I'm the reason
you're hurting.
